Mi Cuba Café is an amazing place to enjoy delicious food and having fun in an excellent atmosphere. The place combines a romantic, stylish and cozy interior. The food is excellent. I highly recommend the cuban pork and the yuca! The prices are reasonable. I highlight the service which is nice and friendly. I reserved the second floor to celebrate my birthday’s party there February 2020 and the service was outstanding! I specially thank Ariel Valladares and his wife for such a beautiful and fantastic night, making sure the food and service were on time. The music is also a plus. Overall my guests and I had a wonderful experience. Highly recommended!!!

We also used the opportunity to ask for a refill of waters (still didn't happen and the bread never came).  After an hour of waiting for the food to come out, we got up to leave. The waitress then argued with us about how we never placed an order to begin with. Other customers expressed frustration about their service as well. Will not be returning.

Only  two or three pieces of the meat were tender and gave me a taste if what it could be like. The yuca in the yuca con mojo was bland and unappealing although the mojo on the side was quite tasty. We went for my boyfriend's birthday because he is half Cuban and misses when he could get Cuban food in Miami all the time. The cafe is very small with little tables all over but just enough space to not feel like you are on top of the table next to you. The servers were very friendly and spoke both English and Spanish. They were very knowledgeable about how good the dishes were made and made great recommendations. The food was delicious and came in big portions so we were full by the end. Then the staff surprised my boyfriend by bringing out a free dessert and singing Happy Birthday. Lovely place and we definitely be back. Parking was about $4 nearby for 2 hours, but it is also a short walk from a metro stop. After fighting DC traffic on a Sunday we will likely take the metro next time.

Mi Cuba Cafe was one of the best/only legit Cuban restaurants in DC that I could find! I used to come here almost every Sunday! All the “cuban” staples here are really good, the Cuban sandwich, the Ropa Vieja, and their Pollo “Mi Cuba”! Let me not forget about the guava and cheese empanada, sooo good! But the past three times I’ve been there, it’s really gone down in quality, some of the newer servers don’t seem to care! The food comes out cold, their water glasses are usually dirty, the wait staff is not attentive. On my last visit I ordered a Cuban sandwich that came out cold, I had taken one bite and told my server, so she took it back to bring me another. She came back with the same sandwich that I had taken a bite out of and touched it in front of me and said, “it’s hot now see”....NEVER COMING BACK HERE AGAIN

Would highly recommend for those who want to grab a bite to go or a date!
